HEADWORD: outward-bound
<hw>outward-bound</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>travelling away from a port
or station; <as>as, <ex>outward-bound</ex> ships</as>. Opposite of
<ant>inward-bound</ant> or <ant>inbound</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> departing(prenominal), outbound, outward.</syn>⟦br⟧
